    "Id": "410394",
    "ThreadId": "201494",
    "Html": "<p>I have just replaced a custom autocomplete box I was using with the WPFToolkit one.&nbsp; I have a grid with a couple textboxes, datepicker, combobox and now autocomplete boxes.&nbsp; when I tab for some reason the autocomplete box is always tabed to last, no matter what the tab index is.&nbsp; Any idea why this might be happening?</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2010-02-26T15:59:52.367-08:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "456781",
    "ThreadId": "201494",
    "Html": "<p>I found a work-around for this issue</p>\r\n<p>I wrapped the AutoCompleteBox in a ContentControl:</p>\r\n<div style=\"color:black;background-color:white\">\r\n<pre><span style=\"color:blue\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">ContentControl</span> <span style=\"color:red\">Margin</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">2</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span> <span style=\"color:red\">Focusable</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">False</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">&gt;</span>\r\n   <span style=\"color:blue\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">toolkit</span><span style=\"color:blue\">:</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">AutoCompleteBox</span> <span style=\"color:red\">x:Name</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">IconFileTextBox</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span> <span style=\"color:red\">Populating</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">IconFileTextBox_Populating</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span> <span style=\"color:red\">Grid.Column</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">0</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span> <span style=\"color:red\">Text</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">{Binding Path=IconFileName, Mode=TwoWay}</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span> <span style=\"color:red\">Padding</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">0</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span> <span style=\"color:red\">Margin</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">0</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span> <span style=\"color:blue\">/&gt;</span>\r\n<span style=\"color:blue\">&lt;/</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">ContentControl</span><span style=\"color:blue\">&gt;</span>\r\n</pre>\r\n<pre>Note that the ContentControl Focusable property is set to False.</pre>\r\n<pre>Now the AutoCompleteBox gets the focus according to the tab index.</pre>\r\n</div>",
